<paragraph blockId="40.[826,1441,198,587]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis box="[826,922,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Identity:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bossuyt F &amp; Dubois A" box="[932,1308,198,220]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref42998" refString="Bossuyt F, Dubois A. 2001. A review of the frog genus Philautus Gistel, 1848 (Amphibia, Anura, Ranidae, Rhacophorinae). Zeylanica 6: 1 - 112." type="journal article" year="2001">Bossuyt &amp; Dubois (2001: 14–15)</bibRefCitation>
provided a detailed review on the nomenclatural history, and considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Boulenger (1882)" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1882" box="[969,1377,259,281]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Ixalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pulcher">
<emphasis box="[969,1146,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Ixalus pulcher</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Boulenger GA" box="[1167,1377,259,281]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" refId="ref43127" refString="Boulenger GA. 1882. Catalogue of the Batrachia Salientia s. Ecaudata in the collection of the British Museum. London: Taylor &amp; Francis." type="book" year="1882">Boulenger (1882)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ahl, 1927" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1927" box="[826,1256,290,312]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Rhacophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcherrimus">
<emphasis box="[826,1136,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Rhacophorus pulcherrimus</emphasis>
Ahl, 1927
</taxonomicName>
as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gunther, 1876" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1876" box="[826,1241,320,342]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Ixalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glandulosus">
<emphasis box="[826,1050,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Ixalus glandulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gunther A" box="[1066,1241,320,342]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" pagination="567 - 577" refId="ref43526" refString="Gunther A. 1876. Third report on collections of Indian reptiles obtained by the British Museum. Proceedings of Zoological Society 1875: 567 - 577." type="journal article" year="1876">Günther, 1876</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. In the original description, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jerdon TC" box="[968,1182,351,373]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" pagination="1486 - 1488" refId="ref43806" refString="Jerdon TC. 1853. Catalogue of reptiles inhabiting the Peninsula of India (continued from p. 479). Journal of Asiatic Society of Bengal 1870: 1486 - 1488." type="journal article" year="1853">Jerdon (1853: 533)</bibRefCitation>
stated the snout–vent length as roughly 
<quantity box="[1036,1137,381,403]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" unit="mm" value="30.5">30.5 mm</quantity>
, and described the unique yellowish colour on the side and limbs (
<figureCitation box="[1273,1354,412,434]" captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="40.[164,243,1359,1378]" captionTargetBox="[168,777,888,1329]" captionTargetId="figure-545@40.[168,777,888,1329]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 34. Neotype of Ixalus glandulosus (BMNH 1947.2.27.22) from ‘Manantavadi’ (i.e. Mananthavady)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445426/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
), which exactly matches with the yellow forelimbs and lateral region of the 
<typeStatus box="[980,1069,474,495]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1882" box="[1106,1216,473,495]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Ixalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pulcher">
<emphasis box="[1106,1216,473,495]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">I. pulcher</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which presently is the 
<typeStatus box="[874,963,504,525]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1876" box="[1005,1170,504,526]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Ixalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glandulosus">
<emphasis box="[1005,1170,504,526]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">I. glandulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Jerdon attributed the species epithet presumably because of its prominently granular (‘glandular’) yellow lateral side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[826,1442,626,1199]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis box="[826,1237,626,648]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jerdon" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[966,1237,626,647]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glandulosus">Philautus glandulosus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from known congeners by the following combination of characters: (1) medium male adult size (SVL 25.2 ± 2.0 mm, 
<emphasis box="[1084,1104,719,740]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">N</emphasis>
= 4); (2) snout pointed; (3) head length shorter than width, HW 10.0 ± 
<quantity box="[1349,1436,749,771]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
, HL 9.2 ± 
<quantity box="[938,1025,779,801]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
, 
<emphasis box="[1041,1061,780,801]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">N</emphasis>
= 4; (4) dorsum shagreened; (5) lateral abdominal area prominently glandular; (6) fingertips rounded; (7) dorsal surface of forearm and loreal region yellow; (8) anterior and posterior surface of thighs yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[826,1442,626,1199]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jerdon" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[851,1113,932,953]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glandulosus">
<emphasis box="[851,1113,932,953]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Philautus glandulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the sole Western Ghats species in the genus with an invariable yellow dorsal surface of forearm and loreal region in life, and creamy white or yellowish in preservation (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1437,1024,1046]" captionStart="Figure 31" captionStartId="38.[164,243,1842,1861]" captionTargetBox="[185,1422,197,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-0@38.[182,1425,194,1813]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="Figure 31. Distribution map. A, Philautus dubois; B, map showing Malabar (shaded in grey), from which the type of Philautus flaviventris was collected; C, Philautus glandulosus; D, Philautus graminirupes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445420/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Figs 31C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[826,856,1055,1076]" captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="40.[164,243,1359,1378]" captionTargetBox="[168,777,888,1329]" captionTargetId="figure-545@40.[168,777,888,1329]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 34. Neotype of Ixalus glandulosus (BMNH 1947.2.27.22) from ‘Manantavadi’ (i.e. Mananthavady)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445426/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">34</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[874,904,1054,1076]" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="40.[164,243,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[168,777,1454,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-558@40.[168,777,1454,1823]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 35. Philautus glandulosus: a specimen from Mananthavady (SDB 40239)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445428/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">35</figureCitation>
). It is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2005" box="[1212,1351,1055,1076]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bobingeri">
<emphasis box="[1212,1351,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">P. bobingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Biju &amp; Bossuyt, 2009" authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2009" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="jayarami" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">P. jayarami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[940,1030,1086,1107]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which it resembles well in overall appearance (
<figureCitation box="[974,1041,1116,1138]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="8.[164,243,799,818]" captionTargetBox="[423,1184,200,767]" captionTargetId="figure-502@8.[419,1187,197,770]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 5. Morphometric distinction between males of four green Philautus species: Z, Philautus akroparallagi sp. nov.; -, Philautus bobingeri; O, Philautus glandulosus; and •, Philautus jayarami sp. nov. The ratio of the snout length (SL)/eye length (EL) is plotted against the snout–vent length SVL (see Table 2)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445368/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). For differences with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2005" box="[1305,1441,1116,1137]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bobingeri">
<emphasis box="[1305,1441,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">P. bobingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Biju &amp; Bossuyt, 2009" authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2009" box="[883,1019,1147,1168]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="jayarami" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[883,1019,1147,1168]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="414">P. jayarami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1033,1127,1147,1168]" pageId="40" pageNumber="414" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, see ‘comparison’ of those species.
</paragraph>
